ce:section.ce:para:
The TEM and DLS result in Fig. 3
                         A and Fig. 3 B, indicate that the AGQDs represent a dot-like structure with a size distribution of 4–9 nm, and the average size is 6 nm. These ultra-small sizes of AGQDs promote more AGQDs to be uniformly dispersed on the PSU support. The AFM results show that the AGQDs have a height of 3 nm, corresponding to 2–3 graphene layers. The FT-IR results reveal the specific functional groups on AGQDs. As shown in Fig. 3C, the peaks at 3447 cm−1, 1715 cm−1 are attributed to the stretching vibration of the hydroxyl group and the stretching vibration of the carbonyl unit in carboxyl groups.[27,28] Both the absorption band at 3016 cm−1 assigned to the stretching vibration of the amine groups (−NH2) and the absorption peak at 2939 cm−1 assigned to the –CH2– vibration are observed in L-Asp and AGQDs, indicating that L-Asp is successfully grafted to AGQDs.[21] Furthermore, the new absorption peak at 1593 cm−1 appears in AGQDs due to the nucleophilic substitution reactions between the amino acid amine groups and the epoxy groups of GQDs.[20] To further confirm the element composition of the AGQDs, the synthesized AGQDs powder was characterized by XPS. Fig. 3D shows the fitting curve of the C1s spectra of AGQDs powder. The peaks of C-C/C=C, -CH2- and O-C=O are located in 284.5 eV, 285 eV, and 288 eV, which indicate the existence of functional groups of AGQDs. Besides, the peak at 286.1 eV corresponded to C-O/C-N was detected in AGQDs, suggesting the successful engagement of L-Asp in the functionalization process.[29–32] AGQDs were further characterized by XRD to analyze the lattice structure. Fig. 3E presents a broad peak (002) at 2θ = 22° that is consistent with the graphite structure.[

                           33

                        ] The zeta potential (Fig. 3F) reveals that the AGQDs is negatively charged in full pH range, owing to the ionization of COOH groups to COO− groups.[

                           28

                        ] Furthermore, the zeta potentials of AGQDs are relatively stable while pH varying from 4 to 10, because [-OOCCH2CH(NH3+)COO−]2− zwitterions from L-Asp are the dominant components at 3.86 < pH < 9.82 according to Li’s work.[

                           34

                        ] The fluorescent images of AGQDs (Fig. 3G) prove that the synthesized AGQDs possess remarkable fluorescence characteristics.
